img src="/assets/img/ts-hw-5.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Our group deployed 28 portable stations across the Tienshan orogen from 20 Aug to 02 Sep 2023.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">WU Hanting and JI Cong have been awarded the CSC</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/csc/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="WU Hanting and JI Cong have been awarded the CSC"/><published>2023-07-27T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-07-27T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/csc</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/csc/"><![CDATA[<p>Drs. WU Hanting and JI Cong have been awarded the Chinese Government Scholarship. They are going to UK and France to study for one year.</p> <p>Congratulations to them! :congratulations:</p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/csc2023-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/csc2023-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/csc2023-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/csc2023.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Drs. WU Hanting and JI Cong have been awarded the Chinese Government Scholarship. They are going to UK and France to study for one year.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">ZHU Yuqi attended the 9th Seismology Algorithm and Program Training Course</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/zyq-nmg/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="ZHU Yuqi attended the 9th Seismology Algorithm and Program Training Course"/><published>2023-07-25T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-07-25T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/zyq-nmg</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/zyq-nmg/"><![CDATA[<p>The course was held between July 24-27, 2023 in Hohhot. It focused on the implementation and practical applications of various seismic algorithms . Topics covered included surface wave tomography, receiver function analysis, earthquake rupture processes, and research on shallow surface structures. Throughout the course, students raised issues they encountered while using the programs, and the developers provided thorough solutions.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The course was held between July 24-27, 2023 in Hohhot. It focused on the implementation and practical applications of various seismic algorithms . Topics covered included surface wave tomography, receiver function analysis, earthquake rupture processes, and research on shallow surface structures. Throughout the course, students raised issues they encountered while using the programs, and the developers provided thorough solutions.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">JI Cong attended the CSRM Meeting held in USTC</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/jc-ustc/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="JI Cong attended the CSRM Meeting held in USTC"/><published>2023-07-20T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-07-20T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/jc-ustc</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/jc-ustc/"><![CDATA[<p>Dr. JI Cong attended the CSRM Meeting held in USTC, Hefei. This meeting discussed the newly published China Seismological Reference Model (CSRM), including the Moho depth, Vp/Vs ratio, Pn velocity, and an integrated model of multiple parameters of the crust and uppermost mantle of China. Further, some results based on this reference model were presented and the system for data exchange was discussed.</p> <p>The CSRM can be achieved online after a simple application on http://chinageorefmodel.org/. The data can be used as a reference model and also the starting model for inversion for further study.</p> <hr/> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/jc-ustc-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/jc-ustc-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/jc-ustc-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/jc-ustc.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Dr. JI Cong attended the CSRM Meeting held in USTC, Hefei. This meeting discussed the newly published China Seismological Reference Model (CSRM), including the Moho depth, Vp/Vs ratio, Pn velocity, and an integrated model of multiple parameters of the crust and uppermost mantle of China. Further, some results based on this reference model were presented and the system for data exchange was discussed.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">ZHU Yuqi gave a talk in Shandong Earthquake Agency</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/Shandong/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="ZHU Yuqi gave a talk in Shandong Earthquake Agency"/><published>2023-07-10T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-07-10T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/Shandong</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/Shandong/"><![CDATA[<p>Yuqi gave a talk about the deep structures and seismotectonics of the southern segment of the Tanlu Fault.</p> <p>China Earthquake Administration posts <a href="https://www.cea.gov.cn/cea/xwzx/xydt/5734732/index.html">this news</a>.</p> <hr/> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/zyq-shandong-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/zyq-shandong-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/zyq-shandong-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/zyq-shandong.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" title="Yuqi@Shandong" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Yuqi gave a talk about the deep structures and seismotectonics of the southern segment of the Tanlu Fault.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">ZHU Yuqi attended the CESS2023 held in Shanghai</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/Shanghai/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="ZHU Yuqi attended the CESS2023 held in Shanghai"/><published>2023-07-07T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-07-07T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/Shanghai</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/Shanghai/"><![CDATA[<p>Yuqi attended the CESS (第七届地球系统科学大会) held in Shanghai.</p> <hr/> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/zyq-shanghai-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/zyq-shanghai-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/zyq-shanghai-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/zyq-shanghai.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" title="Yuqi@Shanghai" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Yuqi attended the CESS (第七届地球系统科学大会) held in Shanghai.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">GENG Jiaqi introduced seismology to high school students</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/gjq-introduction/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="GENG Jiaqi introduced seismology to high school students"/><published>2023-07-05T09:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-07-05T09:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/gjq-introduction</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/2023/gjq-introduction/"><![CDATA[<p>Jiaqi first gave a simple lecture to introduce seismology briefly to high school students who visited Nanjing University and are interested in earth sciences.</p> <hr/> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-xianlin-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-xianlin-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-xianlin-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/gjq-xianlin.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> Afterwards, Jiaqi and the students went around the broad-band seismic station in Xianlin Campus and jumped together strongly to observe the real-time waveforms displayed in the monitor. The students were excited when seeing the "earthquake" they produced. <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-realtime-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-realtime-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-realtime-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/gjq-realtime.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-waveforms-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-waveforms-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/gjq-waveforms-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/gjq-waveforms.jpg" align="middle" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div></div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Jiaqi first gave a simple lecture to introduce seismology briefly to high school students who visited Nanjing University and are interested in earth sciences.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">a post with audios</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/1999/audios/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="a post with audios"/><published>1999-12-31T23:59:59+00:00</published><updated>1999-12-31T23:59:59+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/1999/audios</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/1999/audios/"><![CDATA[<p>This is an example post with audios. It supports local audio files.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <audio src="/assets/audio/epicaly-short-113909.mp3" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <audio src="https://cdn.pixabay.com/download/audio/2022/06/25/audio_69a61cd6d6.mp3" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> A simple, elegant caption looks good between video rows, after each row, or doesn't have to be there at all. </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="sample-posts"/><category term="including"/><category term="audios"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[this is what included audios could look like]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">a post with code</title><link href="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/1999/code/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="a post with code"/><published>1999-12-31T23:59:59+00:00</published><updated>1999-12-31T23:59:59+00:00</updated><id>https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/1999/code</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://ihuangz.github.io/blog/1999/code/"><![CDATA[<p>This theme implements a built-in Jekyll feature, the use of Rouge, for syntax highlighting. It supports more than 100 languages. This example is in C++. All you have to do is wrap your code in markdown code tags:</p> <div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="p">```</span><span class="nl">c++
</span><span class="n">code</span> <span class="n">code</span> <span class="n">code</span>
<span class="p">```</span>
</code></pre></div></div> <div class="language-c++ highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="nf">main</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">argc</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="kt">char</span> <span class="k">const</span> <span class="err">\</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">argv</span><span class="p">[])</span>
<span class="p">{</span>
